<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd" []>
<task xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="creating-dita-documents" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:task.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Creating DITA Documents</title>
  <taskbody>
    <context id="context">
      <p id="create-dita-document-intro"><xref href="types-of-dita-documents.xml">DITA 1.0 and DITA 1.1 documents</xref> can easily be created in Serna by means of ready-made <xref href="serna-document-template.xml">document templates</xref>.</p>
      <p>To create a DITA document, take the following steps:</p>
    </context>
    <steps id="steps">
      <step>
        <cmd>Call up the <keyword>New Document Dialog</keyword>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>To call up the <keyword>New Document Dialog</keyword>, choose <menucascade>
              <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>New Document</uicontrol>
            </menucascade>, or click the <uicontrol>New Document</uicontrol> button <image href="new-document-button.png" align="center"/>on the toolbar, or press <uicontrol>Ctrl-N</uicontrol>.</p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Select a document category.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>From the <uicontrol>Category</uicontrol> list, select <uicontrol>DITA 1.0</uicontrol> or <uicontrol>DITA 1.1</uicontrol>. </p>
          <fig>
            <title>DITA 1.1 Category selected in the New Document Dialog.</title>
            <image href="dita11-selected-in-new-document-dialog.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Select a document template.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>From the <uicontrol>Template</uicontrol> list, select one of the document templates:</p>
        </info>
        <choices>
          <choice>
            <xref href="generic-topic.xml">Topic</xref>
          </choice>
          <choice>
            <xref href="task.xml">Task</xref>
          </choice>
          <choice>
            <xref href="concept.xml">Concept</xref>
          </choice>
          <choice>
            <xref href="glossary.xml">Glossary</xref>
          </choice>
          <choice>
            <xref href="reference.xml">Reference</xref>
          </choice>
          <choice>
            <xref href="composite.xml">Composite</xref>
          </choice>
          <choice>
            <xref href="map.xml">Map</xref>
          </choice>
          <choice>
            <xref href="bookmap.xml">Bookmap</xref>
          </choice>
        </choices>
        <info>
          <fig>
            <title>DITA 1.1 Task Template selected in the New Document Dialog.</title>
            <image href="task-template-selected-in-new-document-dialog.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Specify the filename and location.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>In the <uicontrol>File Name</uicontrol> field, enter the filename. You can use the <uicontrol>Browse</uicontrol> button to specify the file location.</p>
        </info>
        <info>
          <p><note>
              <p>Maps and Bookmaps must have the <filepath>*.ditamap</filepath> extension to be published best.</p>
            </note></p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
    <result>
      <p>A document of the selected type will be created. It will have some pre-defined content including the root element.</p>
    </result>
  </taskbody>
</task>
